<br>
I accompanied a wizzie who wanted to get the Staff of the Wheel.  Our first stop on this ill-fated venture was the great northern expanse outside of Halas.  We dove, and swam to the tunnels underneath the tundra where I learned from tracking that the Lich of Miragul stalked the tunnels.  She was undaunted however, so we proceeded.  As we wandered the tunnels, he came upon us.  I managed to gate before he aggroed me, but the wizard was killed very quickly.  I spent the next hour playing rogue, sneaking through the tunnels looking for her corpse.<br>
<br>
Sneak, as I understand it, works like this.<br>
<br>
It lowers an NPC's aggro radius to almost nothing, but ONLY from behind.  If you're sneaking, you can walk up to an NPC that's KOS to you and if you're behind them, they won't 'notice' you.  It also makes you indifferent, allowing you to conduct transactions with an NPC that faction would normally prevent you from dealing with.  I can't sell to the Frostbone Dwarves in Crystal Caverns normally, but I can sneak behind the merchant and sell.<br>
<br>
Any rogues want to butcher my explanation?  ;)<br>
<br>
 <p>Daeddwin Proudfoot<br>
